\Gamma_0(m)
SL(2,\mathbb{Z})
\sigma_0 = \left( \begin{array}{cc} m & 0 \\ 0 & 1 \end{array} \right) \in C(m)
\Gamma_0(m)=\left\{ \left( \begin{array}{cc} a & b \\ c & d \end{array} \right) \in SL(2, \mathbb{Z} : c \equiv 0 \mod{m} \right\}
C(m) = \left\{ \left( \begin{array}{cc} a & b \\ 0 & d \end{array} \right): ad=m, a>0, 0 \leq b < d, \gcd(a,b,d) = 1 \right\}
\sigma \in C(m)
